    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-26T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/471: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-26T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 26, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 26—1:50 a.m]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>402. Foreign Office has just telephoned that negative Japanese note on British
                    memorandum has been delivered and a copy will be forwarded me this evening.<note
                        n="60" xml:id="d104fn60">For text of Japanese <hi rend="italic"
                            >aide-mémoire</hi>, see <ref target="#pg_102">p. 102</ref>.</note> In
                    the meantime they ask urgently whether a copy of my memorandum to them based on
                    your 211, August 14, 7 p.m., may be made available to the Japanese and French,
                    and the press informed [of] its existence. In the latter case kindly indicate
                        <pb facs="0202" n="100" xml:id="pg_100"/> whether, and if so, how much of
                    its contents may be made public. The British hope for an answer that will enable
                    them to make the press announcement tomorrow morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
